http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/%E2%80%98Exempt-us-from-Gurgaon-Faridabad-toll%E2%80%99/article14026594.ece

A large number of people from over half-a-dozen villages near Gurgaon staged a demonstration on Gurgaon-Faridabad Road here on Wednesday demanding exemption from paying the toll.The protesters, who had assembled at a vacant plot near the toll plaza around noon, raised slogans and contended that the toll road was built on their land and hence they should be exempted from paying the toll.Currently, cars are charged Rs.20 per trip and Rs.30 for a round trip. Similarly, heavy vehicles are charged Rs.60 per trip and Rs.90 for round trip.